network.messaging

Interface MessagePipeline.MessageContext

  • Enclosing class:
    MessagePipeline

    public static interface MessagePipeline.MessageContext
    a custom context in which commands can be executed. Messages that arrive from the associated entity will first be routed to the context. The context can then choose to consume the message or ignore it. If it is ignored, the message will go to the default context for all world messages.
